r</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">)</a> =&gt; <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">(</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">acc</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array.toList\">toList</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAppend.hAppend\">++</a> <span class=\"fn\">l</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">)</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeList_eq_takeListTR.go","kind":"theorem","line":869,"name":"List.takeList_eq_takeListTR.go","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L869-L872"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeList_eq_takeListTR\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">takeList_eq_takeListTR</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\">@<a href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeList\">takeList</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> @<a href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeListTR\">takeListTR</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeList_eq_takeListTR","kind":"theorem","line":867,"name":"List.takeList_eq_takeListTR","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L867-L873"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeListTR.go\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">takeListTR</span>.<span class=\"name\">go</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">√ó</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Auxiliary for `takeListTR`: `takeListTR.go as as' acc = acc.toList ++ takeList as as'`. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeListTR.go","kind":"def","line":861,"name":"List.takeListTR.go","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L861-L865"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeListTR\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">takeListTR</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">xs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ns</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">√ó</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Tail-recursive version of `takeList`. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeListTR","kind":"def","line":857,"name":"List.takeListTR","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L857-L865"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeList\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">takeList</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">√ó</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`takeList as ns` extracts successive sublists from `as`. For `ns = n‚āĀ ... n‚āė`,\nit first takes the `n‚āĀ` initial elements from `as`, then the next `n‚āā` ones,\netc. It returns the sublists of `as` -- one for each `nŠĶĘ` -- and the remaining\nelements of `as`. If `as` does not have at least as many elements as the sum of\nthe `nŠĶĘ`, the corresponding sublists will have less than `nŠĶĘ` elements.\n```\ntakeList ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e'] [2, 1, 1] = ([['a', 'b'], ['c'], ['d']], ['e'])\ntakeList ['a', 'b'] [3, 1] = ([['a', 'b'], []], [])\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.takeList","kind":"def","line":839,"name":"List.takeList","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L839-L855"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.fillNones\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">fillNones</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`fillNones xs ys` replaces the `none`s in `xs` with elements of `ys`. If there\nare not enough `ys` to replace all the `none`s, the remaining `none`s are\ndropped from `xs`.\n```\nfillNones [none, some 1, none, none] [2, 3] = [2, 1, 3]\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.fillNones","kind":"def","line":824,"name":"List.fillNones","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L824-L837"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.allSome\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">allSome</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">l</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If all elements of `xs` are `some xŠĶĘ`, `allSome xs` returns the `xŠĶĘ`. Otherwise\nit returns `none`.\n```\nallSome [some 1, some 2] = some [1, 2]\nallSome [some 1, none  ] = none\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.allSome","kind":"def","line":814,"name":"List.allSome","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L814-L822"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.zipRight\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">zipRight</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ő≤</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">ő≤</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">√ó</a> <span class=\"fn\">ő≤</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Right-biased version of `List.zip`. `zipRight as bs` returns the list of pairs\n`(aŠĶĘ, bŠĶĘ)` for `aŠĶĘ ‚ąą as` and `bŠĶĘ ‚ąą bs`. If `as` is shorter than `bs`, the\nremaining `bŠĶĘ` are paired with `none`.\n```\nzipRight [1, 2] ['a'] = [(some 1, 'a')]\nzipRight [1] ['a', 'b'] = [(some 1, 'a'), (none, 'b')]\nzipRight = zipWithRight prod.mk\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.zipRight","kind":"def","line":802,"name":"List.zipRight","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L802-L812"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.zipLeft\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">zipLeft</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ő≤</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">ő≤</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">√ó</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">ő≤</span></span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Left-biased version of `List.zip`. `zipLeft as bs` returns the list of pairs\n`(aŠĶĘ, bŠĶĘ)` for `aŠĶĘ ‚ąą as` and `bŠĶĘ ‚ąą bs`. If `bs` is shorter than `as`, the\nremaining `aŠĶĘ` are paired with `none`.\n```\nzipLeft [1, 2] ['a'] = [(1, some 'a'), (2, none)]\nzipLeft [1] ['a', 'b'] = [(1, some 'a')]\nzipLeft = zipWithLeft prod.mk\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.zipLeft","kind":"def","line":790,"name":"List.zipLeft","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L790-L800"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.zipWithRight\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">zipWithRight</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ő≤</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ő≥</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">ő≤</span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\">ő≥</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">as</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">bs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">ő≤</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">ő≥</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Right-biased version of `List.zipWith`. `zipWithRight f as bs` applies `f` to each\npair `aŠĶĘ ‚ąą as` and `bŠĶĘ ‚ÄĆ‚ąą bs`. If `as` is shorter than `bs`, `f` is applied to\n`none` for the remaining `bŠĶĘ`.\n```\nzipWithRight prod.mk [1, 2] ['a'] = [(some 1, 'a')]\nzipWithRight prod.mk [1] ['a', 'b'] = [(some 1, 'a'), (none, 'b')]\nzipWithRight f as bs = (zipWithRight' f as bs).fst\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.zipWithRight","kind":"def","line":777,"name":"List.zipWithRight","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L777-L788"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.zipWithLeft_eq_zipWithLeftTR.go\"><s