></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"List of all sections through a list of lists. A section\nof `[L‚āĀ, L‚āā, ..., L‚āô]` is a list whose first element comes from\n`L‚āĀ`, whose second element comes from `L‚āā`, and so on.\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.sections","kind":"def","line":418,"name":"List.sections","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L418-L425"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.transpose.go\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">transpose</span>.<span class=\"name\">go</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">l</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">acc</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`go : List őĪ ‚Üí Array (List őĪ) ‚Üí Array (List őĪ)` handles the insertion of\na new list into all the lists in the array:\n`go [a, b, c] #[l‚āĀ, l‚āā, l‚āÉ] = #[a::l‚āĀ, b::l‚āā, c::l‚āÉ]`.\nIf the new list is too short, the later lists are unchanged, and if it is too long\nthe array is extended:\n```\ngo [a] #[l‚āĀ, l‚āā, l‚āÉ] = #[a::l‚āĀ, l‚āā, l‚āÉ]\ngo [a, b, c, d] #[l‚āĀ, l‚āā, l‚āÉ] = #[a::l‚āĀ, b::l‚āā, c::l‚āÉ, [d]]\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.transpose.go","kind":"def","line":414,"name":"List.transpose.go","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/3881bc95874e5843b76886ea136f4722f1fa83cf/Batteries/Data/List/Basic.lean#L414-L416"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Data/List/Basic.html#List.transpose.pop\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">transpose</span>.<span class=\"name\">pop</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">old</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span> ‚Üí <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">√ó</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">őĪ</span></span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`pop : List őĪ ‚Üí StateM (List őĪ) (List őĪ)` transforms the input list `old`\nby taking the head of the current state and pushing it on the head of `old`.\nIf the state list is empty, then `o